widgets_values:
Batch prompts on .txt file

You can create a batch of prompts, save it on a .txt file and use that file for automatic image generation.

The .txt file must be formatted as follow (as example with just 2 prompts):


positive: a girl is walking through street, raincoat, yellow umbrella

negative: (leave empty)

-------

positive:museum, people are looking paintings, abstract

negative: (leave empty)

-------


The file has to be saved in the following folder:

/custom_nodes/ComfyUI-Inspire-Pack/prompts/example/

widgets_values:
--The original FLUX model--

This workflow was designed for the original FLUX model released by the Black Forest Lab team.  You will need the following files to use the workflow:

1) UNET - Dev or Schnell version (each one is around 24Gb, Dev gives better results, Schnell is the "turbo" version).
Dev download Link: https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-dev/resolve/main/flux1-dev.safetensors?download=true
Schnell download LinK:
https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-schnell/resolve/main/flux1-schnell.safetensors?download=true

2) Clip - you need these clip files (use fp16 for better results, fp8 if you have low Vram/Ram).

t5xxl_fp16:
https://huggingface.co/comfyanonymous/flux_text_encoders/resolve/main/t5xxl_fp16.safetensors?download=true

t5xxl_fp8:
https://huggingface.co/comfyanonymous/flux_text_encoders/resolve/main/t5xxl_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors?download=true

clip_l:
https://huggingface.co/comfyanonymous/flux_text_encoders/resolve/main/clip_l.safetensors?download=true



3) VAE - last but not least the VAE file:
https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-dev/resolve/main/ae.safetensors?download=true

nodes.title: Unnamed
widgets_values:
--Face Detailer--

This detailer will enhance the face's skin details according to the prompt you use in it.
It uses a SD 1.5 checkpoint and LoRA to get more realistic results, as FLUX's LoRA's are still just a few and not perfectly trained yet.
These are the files you need for the mask detector:

1) Epicrealism SD 1.5 checkpoint (goes in folder /models/checkpoints/ )

https://huggingface.co/Justin-Choo/epiCRealism-Natural_Sin_RC1_VAE/resolve/main/epicrealism_naturalSinRC1VAE.safetensors?download=true

2)More details SD 1.5 LoRA (goes in folder /models/loras/ )

https://civitai.com/models/82098/add-more-details-detail-enhancer-tweaker-lora

3) sam_vit_b_01ec64.pth (goes in folder /models/ultralytics/bbox/ )

https://huggingface.co/datasets/Gourieff/ReActor/blob/main/models/sams/sam_vit_b_01ec64.pth

4) face_yolov8n_v2.pt (goes in folder /models/ultralytics/bbox/ )

https://huggingface.co/Bingsu/adetailer/blob/main/face_yolov8n_v2.pt

5) eyeful_v2-paired.pt (goes in folder /models/ultralytics/bbox/ )

https://civitai.com/models/178518/eyeful-or-robust-eye-detection-for-adetailer-comfyui

----------
You can use different checkpoint /lora files if you want to test them, both SD1.5 and SDXL should work.

nodes.title: Unnamed
widgets_values:
Tenofas FLUX-LoRA's and Upscaler v.3.3

This workflow is very easy to use.
Just load your FLUX model, your LoRA's, chose how to prompt (txt2img, img2img or LLM) run it, compare the Flux (with or without LoRA's) image with the image that went through Face Detailer and decide if you want to use the Ultimate SD Upscaler on any of the two images (it may take very long to complete the upscaling).

Link to Workflow guide:

https://civitai.com/articles/6848/tenofas-flux-modular-workflow-user-guide

----

You can control:
1. The prompt (choose the way to prompt in the Prompt selector)
2. Flux Guidance (3.5 is the standard)
3. LoRA's weights 
4. Sampler and Scheduler
5. Image size
6. Basic upscale (if not interested set it to 1.0)
7. Seed (fixed or random)
8. Face Detailer settings

Generated images will appear in the Preview Chooser node and in the large Image Compare node (both are saved).
If you want to use the Ultimate SD Upscaler you just need to click on the image you want to upascale and send (Progress selected image) it to the upscaler.
In the Ultimate SD Upscaler group you can select your Upscaler model and all the settings of the upscale.


----

Workflow:
1. FLUX Model Loader
Set the FLUX model, its weight and Clip you want to use.
2. FLUX LoRA's settings
Choose the LoRA's you want to use and set their weights.
3. Image size and upscale
Set the size of your image (you can set a fast upscale here too)
4. Prompt and FluxGuidance
Input your prompt.  I suggest to be very descriptive, don't use comma-separated tokens, just write plain english text.  Set FluxGuidance (3.5 is the standard value)
5. Flux sampler and scheduler
Select the sampler and scheduler you want to use.
6. Ultimate SD Upscaler
Set the upscale parameters.
7. Hit "Queue Prompt" to start the generation process.
8. Compare the two images and decide if you want to send one to the upscaler or just generate a new image.
8. Wait and enjoy your image!

widgets_values: A professional photo portrait of an elderly man with a white beard and mustache. He is wearing a black jacket and a flat cap.

I'm delighted to help you describe this portrait! Here's a possible description:

The portrait features an elderly gentleman with a dignified and distinguished appearance. His white beard and mustache are well-groomed, adding to his sage-like demeanor. He is clad in a black jacket that fits him perfectly, exuding an air of sophistication and elegance. A flat cap rests on his head, giving him a classic and timeless look. His piercing eyes, full of wisdom and character, captivate the viewer, drawing them into his life story. The background is minimal, allowing the subject to be the main focus of the portrait. The overall impression is one of a man who has lived a full life and has many tales to tell.
